The output is an integer representing the minimum number of boxes touching the floor.
The boxes are placed in the storeroom according to the given rules.
Each box is a cube with a side length of 1 unit.
The width, length, and height of the storeroom are all equal to `n` units.
The boxes are placed anywhere on the floor of the storeroom.
If box `x` is placed on top of box `y`, each side of the four vertical sides of box `y` must either be adjacent to another box or to a wall.
